</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/utheneogenesis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TheNeoGenesis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/8/02 7:30:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10809.topic&index=50>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://lunar.damnsw.net/~tng/hotlink/headshot.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: =)!</span><hr size=1> yea, spoiler crap**<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Actually, the crop circles weren't signs... They were maps. The only times the word &quot;signs&quot; was used was in the sentences where &quot;miricales&quot; were also used. In the end the signs were the signs from God. <br>
It's pretty deep when you think about it. I never thought of a movie combining God and aliens. Much less God saving man from aliens, but heck... it was very good anyway. The mix was interesting and very well done.<br>
<br>
I figured the crop circles were signs too, like warning from the aliens or something but the fact that it was something completely different only added to the movie. It was a great idea. Props to the writer.<br>
<br>
It was brilliant to have the movie closed within the confines of the house for the most part. It's like, what was going on in Joe Blow's house during ID4. We're so used to movies where we know everything that's going on because the main character is with the FBI or some other branch of government or because he's a big time scientist. But no one enver thought to make a movie from a Preacher's perspective as he's chillin on his farm. heh.<br>
<br>
The movie was very well done. I don't know if it should be called Religious, Super Natural or Sci-fi. But for now I'll call it a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Super Natural Sci-Fi Thriller w/religious over-tones</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> you just can't beat that.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
And yes, Mel Gibson was excellent.<br>
<br>
**edit**<br>
They left too much room open for a part two. Please, for the love of all things sacred, let there be no part two!<br>
But how about one of the last statements that the aliens turned back because they had been defeated by &quot;primative methods in the middle east&quot;. Now we know it wasn't water because, c'mon, there IS NO water in the middle east. lol<br>
It would be really interesting to know what methods were used. I'm thinking it's prayer, because one of the only other comments from CNN or whoever before communications were shut down was that &quot;people are flocking to churches, may God be with us.&quot;<br>
I heard the word &quot;religious movie&quot; when I was watching some reviews of signs, but i had no idea... on the surface, no, but when you see what the writer was actually doing it's rather stunning. <br>
Of course, he can flip the script and make it a higher alien power giving the signs and all that but I seriously doubt it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><p align="center"> <a align="center" href="http://theneogenesis.com/index.htm" target="_blank"> 
